review_blob:
Medium hops, nice malts, great with cheese, crackers, bread etc. Really balanced ale.

beer_name: Four Mile Tight Head Best British

review_blob:
Great fruity, hoppy nose. Great pale session ale. Nice addition to driftwoods line up.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice to have a pale ale that's a little more traditional from this area. I find most west coast ones always go to heavy on the cascade hops. This is subtle. Not heavy bubbles, little heavy on the back of the palate. Would have it again.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice and malty, good hops. Spice on the back end. Light Amber colouring. Sweet fruit on the nose.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Great golden colour, nice nose. After taste is a little bitter and confused from the ancho chilies and Szechuan peppercorns. My problem with beers from New Belgium Brewing is they try and say they are influenced by Belgian beers but they are far from it. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Steamworks / New Belgium Rollin Golden Belgian Ale

review_blob:
Exactly what you think it will be like. Heavy chocolate and orange. Great for the winter holiday season.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Beautiful sipper. Love the malty flavour and just rolled off the palate. Drinking a 5 year old. Amber, great malts on the nose. Highly recommend aging.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Beautiful orange colour. Fruity on the nose. Little sour on the palate. Really A well done Belgian style beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Granted we are drinking this beer bought in 1999 so its 14 years old. A pale lager, still nice white head as it pours. Very yeasty. Nice colour. Light. Good for a muggy day.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Great looking white IPA. Thick and bitter. I liked it for what is was but would not buy again. Stays long on the palate. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Dead Frog Furious Friar Belgian IPA

review_blob:
Drinking a 5 year old. Beautiful flavour. Has great syrup consistency, would be great on ice cream. Almost like a port for taste. Light carbonation, caramel in colour. Just a great beer!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Drinking an 8 year old aged one, holds up incredibly well. Amazing nose, does not have the head anymore but an absolute delight. Great malty taste on the palate. Golden colour. Light carbonation. Recommend. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice pale ale. Im doing this review by a bottle but this is a far nicer beer by the tap in my opinion. Medium body with nice balance of hops and malt. A step above many regular pales out there.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Belgian style white ale, yellow/gold colour. Silky white head that lasts. Citrus nose with both bitter and sweet taste on the palate. Really enjoyed this summer sipper that does not taste like it's 7.5% alc.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Summer beer. Great colour, crisp and clean. Not a big nose. Light hint of apricot. Not sweet at all.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice that its not an American style IPA. To many beers have been over hopped. This beer is not one of those. Nice malts. Great sweetness on the back end. Light white head. Amber colour. Smooth and light with a little carbonation. Good barrel beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Great spring/summer beer. Citrus and sour notes. A little closer to a Wit then a Saison I believe.

Very Smokey. Almost to much. Shared between 3 of us. Could not have a whole bottle. Very much a food beer.
